    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>II. SIGNAL CONDITIONER</title>
        <para>It conditions the input signals for the internal microprocessor
            <emph type="bold">(Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1250503">1.16</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            ).
            <emph type="bold"></emph>This enables the microprocessor to interpret the signals.
            <emph type="bold"></emph>Signal conditioning usually consists of converting analog signals to digital
            signals, squaring up sine wave signals or amplifying low intensity signals to a level the ECM microprocessor
            can process.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef1250503" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1100" filename="../figeg1/EG1100.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 1.16 - Electronic Control Module Signal Conditioning</caption>
